{"TopicId":177054,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"What does it take to make a mod from scratch?","CreatedByName":"I likeOxidizerrfuel","CreatedById":190738,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-25T20:11:32Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"I likeOxidizerrfuel","CreatedById":190738,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-25T20:11:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat tools or programs do you need to make a mod or a plugin?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FireKerb","CreatedById":176562,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-26T07:27:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ll quote something from another thread.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223420678\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022176934\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221532349316\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022146521\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Phineas Freak\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 7/23/2018 at 10:35 PM, Phineas Freak said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is an editor for part models:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022#\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/a\u003E \u003Cspan\u003EReveal hidden contents\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4d/Blender_2.79.png/1200px-Blender_2.79.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u00221200px-Blender_2.79.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 height=\u0022595\u0022 src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4d/Blender_2.79.png/1200px-Blender_2.79.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is an editor for part textures:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022#\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/a\u003E \u003Cspan\u003EReveal hidden contents\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://1.bp.blogspot.com/-rsm1R2rOrLs/Ue0zDb2hO1I/AAAAAAAAGTo/l8qa5HeEfMU/s1600/0.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u00220.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 height=\u0022546\u0022 src=\u0022https://1.bp.blogspot.com/-rsm1R2rOrLs/Ue0zDb2hO1I/AAAAAAAAGTo/l8qa5HeEfMU/s1600/0.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd this is an editor for part modules:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022#\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/a\u003E \u003Cspan\u003EReveal hidden contents\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"4x4cheesecake","CreatedById":187982,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-26T07:47:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo add some informations:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDepending on the type of mod/plugin you want to create, you will need different tools:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n-If you want to create new parts, you will need Blender to create the 3D model and an IDE of your choice (i.e. Visual Studio) to write the code. The code must be written in C#.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n-If you want to create new textures, you need a graphics editor like photoshop. AFAIK, you don\u0027t need to write some code but a ModuleManager patch.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n-If you want to create new game mechanics or modify existing features, you will need an IDE of your choice and the code must be written in C#.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n-If you want to modify existing parts, you will need a texteditor and ModuleManager \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E (at least, this should be the easiest solution)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you already know what kind of mod you want to create, I would suggest to read through the \u0027Add-on Development\u0027 subforum. There are several tutorials, additional tools and people who are willing to help you \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/forum/36-add-on-development/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Ehttps://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/forum/36-add-on-development/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sumghai","CreatedById":66272,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-26T09:05:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#27ae60;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E[MOD - Moved to Add-on Discussions.]\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}